1
00:00:01,668 --> 00:00:03,086
In the previous episode,

2
00:00:03,111 --> 00:00:05,339
the first match of
the national tournament

3
00:00:05,573 --> 00:00:08,296
between Nankatsu
and Meiwa started.

4
00:00:08,818 --> 00:00:11,737
Tsubasa fooled Kojiro
with a spectacular lob

5
00:00:11,762 --> 00:00:14,473
and scored the first goal of
the match with ease.

6
00:00:14,782 --> 00:00:15,574
Later, Kojiro kicked

7
00:00:15,599 --> 00:00:17,351
a powerful shot
towards Yuzo,

8
00:00:17,476 --> 00:00:18,977
hitting him with the ball
into the goal.

9
00:00:19,002 --> 00:00:20,504
The second goal
to tie the match.

10
00:00:20,829 --> 00:00:22,623
Unfortunately,
Kojiro's last shot

11
00:00:22,648 --> 00:00:24,233
struck fear into
Yuzo's spirits,

12
00:00:24,258 --> 00:00:26,135
making him unable
to guard his goal.

13
00:00:27,653 --> 00:00:30,072
-Yuzo, do something!
-Stop the ball!

14
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:33,283
That was
a great play, Tsubasa!

15
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:35,202
You see, Yuzo?

16
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,829
The ball is our friend,
so don't fear it!

17
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:38,997
What?

18
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:41,542
You think
the ball's your friend, huh?

19
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:42,668
Well, if that's the case...

20
00:00:42,994 --> 00:00:44,662
Here it is!
Kiss it!

21
00:00:44,687 --> 00:00:45,521
Be careful, Tsubasa!

22
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:46,672
Be careful!

23
00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:49,967
The ball hits
Tsubasa in the face!

24
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:51,885
What?

25
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:53,470
No! Tsubasa!

26
00:00:55,931 --> 00:00:58,225
See? There's no need
to fear it!

27
00:00:59,852 --> 00:01:01,186
Thank you, Tsubasa.

28
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:03,063
I will defend the goal!

29
00:01:03,397 --> 00:01:05,190
-Now, I won't be afraid!
-That's it.

30
00:01:05,369 --> 00:01:07,163
This time
you won't save it!

31
00:01:08,377 --> 00:01:09,920
-Good job, Yuzo, you did it!
-Good job, Yuzo, you did it!

32
00:01:09,945 --> 00:01:10,946
Yes!

33
00:01:11,220 --> 00:01:13,552
The ball is my best friend!

34
00:01:14,116 --> 00:01:15,576
I won't ever let it go!

35
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:17,369
That twerp did it again!

36
00:01:17,765 --> 00:01:20,642
He got his goalie
to regain his confidence!

37
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:22,916
Here you are, Tsubasa!

38
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,585
Take good care of
our friend!

39
00:01:25,146 --> 00:01:28,100
Yes! Now it's our turn
to attack!

40
00:01:30,048 --> 00:01:35,053
[opening theme]

41
00:03:13,503 --> 00:03:16,422
Episode 15:
I Can't Lose Because It's My Dream!

42
00:03:16,572 --> 00:03:18,198
Here we are live at
the national tournament.

43
00:03:18,223 --> 00:03:20,050
The first half of the match
is almost done

44
00:03:20,075 --> 00:03:22,828
and the scoreboard's
at 1-2 in favor of Meiwa.

45
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:24,830
Nankatsu is pressured into
having to tie the match.

46
00:03:24,855 --> 00:03:26,440
Tsubasa has the ball
and initiates the attack.

47
00:03:26,675 --> 00:03:27,968
I'm counting on you,
Taro!

48
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,084
You got it!

49
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:30,794
This time around,
we're gonna show them

50
00:03:30,794 --> 00:03:31,895
that we're friends
with the ball

51
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:32,963
and we're not afraid.

52
00:03:32,988 --> 00:03:34,782
Don't get
too friendly, punk.

53
00:03:34,807 --> 00:03:36,517
I don't want them
getting through you.

54
00:03:36,542 --> 00:03:37,919
Stop them right now!

55
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,201
-Yes!
-Yes!

56
00:03:39,226 --> 00:03:40,602
I won't let you score!

57
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:42,306
It's all yours, Taro!

58
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:43,891
Tsubasa!

59
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:44,992
Here it comes.

60
00:03:45,017 --> 00:03:47,411
Nankatsu's famous
golden duo's combination,

61
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:48,854
Tsubasa Ozora
and Taro Misaki,

62
00:03:48,854 --> 00:03:51,023
pass the ball to each other
in perfect synchronization,

63
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:52,858
getting closer
to Meiwa's goal.

64
00:03:52,858 --> 00:03:54,234
Huh? No!

65
00:03:54,259 --> 00:03:55,903
Come and try to get
the ball if you can.

66
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:57,029
Yeah!

67
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:59,072
No, I won't let you shoot.

68
00:03:59,097 --> 00:04:01,099
Kojiro Hyuga
gets closer to Tsubasa

69
00:04:01,124 --> 00:04:03,118
and tries to intercept
the ball from Taro Misaki.

70
00:04:03,143 --> 00:04:04,269
You're mine.

71
00:04:06,702 --> 00:04:07,703
What?

72
00:04:07,728 --> 00:04:09,483
Simply incredible!

73
00:04:09,508 --> 00:04:11,335
Taro Misaki fools Hyuga,

74
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,409
who doesn't make it
to the ball

75
00:04:12,434 --> 00:04:14,436
and it goes directly
to Tsubasa.

76
00:04:14,596 --> 00:04:15,597
It doesn't matter
who kicks it,

77
00:04:15,622 --> 00:04:16,623
I'll stop anyone!

78
00:04:16,926 --> 00:04:18,928
Let's score on them
with our friend, Taro!

79
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:20,944
And now,
Tsubasa returns the favor

80
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,030
to Taro with
a crossover pass.

81
00:04:23,055 --> 00:04:23,972
No, this can't be.

82
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:26,112
And here comes Misaki
with a volley and...

83
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:29,811
Goal!

84
00:04:30,588 --> 00:04:32,590
Team Nankatsu ties
the match with two-all

85
00:04:32,887 --> 00:04:34,556
just before the end
of the first half.

86
00:04:35,237 --> 00:04:37,190
Great teamwork, Taro!

87
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:38,070
-Thank you, it was
-What a shot!

88
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,280
-a great pass, Tsubasa!

89
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:43,784
Good job, Taro!
That's how it's done!

90
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:45,953
And with that whistle,

91
00:04:45,978 --> 00:04:48,764
the first half ends with
a two-all draw

92
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:49,790
on the scoreboard.

93
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,417
-You're the best! Yeah!
-You're the best! Yeah!

94
00:04:52,442 --> 00:04:54,670
Tsubasa, Taro!

95
00:04:55,172 --> 00:04:56,855
Yeah! We tied.

96
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,215
-You guys did it!
-That was great, man!

97
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,801
-You two are a great duo!
-That was incredible!

98
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:08,934
Very interesting.

99
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:10,502
I have no idea
who's going to win.

100
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:11,854
NANKATSU SC

101
00:05:11,854 --> 00:05:13,564
NANKATSU SC
Team, you were incredible.

102
00:05:13,564 --> 00:05:13,939
Team, you were incredible.

103
00:05:14,108 --> 00:05:15,568
Great work, Tsubasa.

104
00:05:15,602 --> 00:05:17,271
That means a lot, Ryo.
Thank you.

105
00:05:17,296 --> 00:05:18,836
Great work out there,
everyone.

106
00:05:18,861 --> 00:05:19,444
Huh?

107
00:05:19,469 --> 00:05:20,928
You were able to
tie the match.

108
00:05:20,953 --> 00:05:21,871
-Thank you!
-Thank you!

109
00:05:22,158 --> 00:05:24,035
Hey, Yuzo, think you can
handle the cage?

110
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,158
Of course, Coach.

111
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:26,451
Don't you worry about that.

112
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,328
I'll protect it for us.

113
00:05:28,805 --> 00:05:30,014
I'll protect it for my life.

114
00:05:30,484 --> 00:05:31,485
-That's right!
-That's right!

115
00:05:31,652 --> 00:05:32,778
That's exactly it!

116
00:05:32,803 --> 00:05:34,805
If we want to win this,
we'll have to attack.

117
00:05:35,252 --> 00:05:36,503
I want you to
score more goals.

118
00:05:36,528 --> 00:05:37,070
You got that?

119
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:38,755
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

120
00:05:39,548 --> 00:05:40,549
Damn it all!

121
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,885
Listen up! I want you
to pass me the ball.

122
00:05:42,885 --> 00:05:43,886
Huh?

123
00:05:43,911 --> 00:05:45,621
We have to score on them.

124
00:05:45,646 --> 00:05:47,272
I'll do it
any way I have to.

125
00:05:47,469 --> 00:05:49,596
I'm going to take care of
those two pesky twerps.

126
00:05:50,517 --> 00:05:52,769
I'll show them
that my skill is superior.

127
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:53,812
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

128
00:05:53,924 --> 00:05:56,093
That young kid,
Tsubasa Ozora...

129
00:05:56,118 --> 00:05:58,662
He's helped light the fire
in Kojiro's heart.

130
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:01,111
Hey, listen to me,
Kojiro.

131
00:06:01,343 --> 00:06:03,345
Listen up.
Offense is the best defense.

132
00:06:03,626 --> 00:06:04,956
You need to release
all of your strength.

133
00:06:04,981 --> 00:06:06,649
-You hear me?
-All right, Coach!

134
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,954
I didn't come all
the way here just to lose.

135
00:06:10,979 --> 00:06:13,649
Especially not...
to those two.

136
00:06:15,323 --> 00:06:16,793
Everyone is
giving it their all

137
00:06:16,793 --> 00:06:18,587
to make up for
your absence on the pitch,

138
00:06:18,612 --> 00:06:20,088
-don't you think?
-Yes!

139
00:06:20,506 --> 00:06:21,882
That's right, everyone.

140
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:23,425
You can handle
the second half.

141
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:25,886
Win this.
I know that you can do it.

142
00:06:27,007 --> 00:06:27,924
Genzo...

143
00:06:27,949 --> 00:06:29,618
I know you wish
to be out there,

144
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:31,251
but you must
be patient.

145
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,602
You can't help
in your condition.

146
00:06:33,995 --> 00:06:36,060
The players are now
returning to the pitch.

147
00:06:36,085 --> 00:06:38,004
And the second half
is about to start.

148
00:06:38,888 --> 00:06:40,390
For sure in
the second half...

149
00:06:40,917 --> 00:06:42,169
...we'll find out
who the best team is

150
00:06:42,194 --> 00:06:43,170
between them.

151
00:06:43,195 --> 00:06:44,154
You can do it.

152
00:06:44,179 --> 00:06:45,764
Tsubasa versus Kojiro...

153
00:06:46,093 --> 00:06:47,887
Don't get discouraged.
You got this, Taro.

154
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,869
Which of the two will
come out on top?

155
00:06:51,184 --> 00:06:52,727
Will it be Tsubasa Ozora?

156
00:06:52,752 --> 00:06:54,086
Or Kojiro Hyuga?

157
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:57,434
From now on,
I'll show you

158
00:06:57,459 --> 00:06:59,670
my real style of play,
Tsubasa.

159
00:06:59,695 --> 00:07:01,030
So you'd better
be ready.

160
00:07:02,651 --> 00:07:04,716
And the second half starts.

161
00:07:04,942 --> 00:07:06,276
Team Meiwa
initiates the attack,

162
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:08,403
but the pass is intercepted
by Taro Misaki

163
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:09,471
from Team Nankatsu.

164
00:07:09,496 --> 00:07:11,306
Taro Misaki runs
with Mamoru Izawa

165
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:13,617
and Teppei Kisugi
towards the danger zone.

166
00:07:13,642 --> 00:07:15,477
These three players
are running a fast break.

167
00:07:15,531 --> 00:07:16,240
Nankatsu is switching
to offense.

168
00:07:16,265 --> 00:07:17,409
Get the ball back!

169
00:07:17,434 --> 00:07:18,435
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

170
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:20,421
Two players from
Meiwa slide tackle,

171
00:07:20,858 --> 00:07:23,729
but Taro Misaki manages to
keep control of the ball.

172
00:07:24,292 --> 00:07:26,655
This is as far as you go!

173
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,907
Kojiro Hyuga
gets the ball back,

174
00:07:28,932 --> 00:07:30,182
knocking down Misaki.

175
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,200
It looked a bit harsh,

176
00:07:31,325 --> 00:07:32,368
but it's not against
the rules.

177
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:34,036
My style is better
than yours.

178
00:07:34,203 --> 00:07:35,496
So you two should
watch and learn.

179
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,289
Huh?

180
00:07:36,455 --> 00:07:37,498
I'm warning you...

181
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:40,626
You'll wish you had lost
since the very beginning.

182
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,378
You won't get past me.

183
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:44,422
Nankatsu attempts
to recover the ball...

184
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:48,693
but receives a direct
hit from Kojiro Hyuga.

185
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:49,886
Mamoru, no!

186
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,387
Takeshi!

187
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:53,347
Hyuga passes
to Takeshi Sawada

188
00:07:53,472 --> 00:07:55,099
and runs towards
the opponent's goal.

189
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:56,350
Captain!

190
00:07:56,475 --> 00:07:58,311
Takeshi Sawada sends
a crossover pass.

191
00:07:58,436 --> 00:07:59,353
I will stop it.

192
00:07:59,478 --> 00:08:00,688
I'm not afraid of you,
Kojiro.

193
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,107
Say your prayers!

194
00:08:04,164 --> 00:08:05,624
Kojiro Hyuga kicks and...

195
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:08,529
What a goal from Meiwa!

196
00:08:08,854 --> 00:08:11,190
This time, instead of aiming
towards the goalkeeper,

197
00:08:11,215 --> 00:08:13,009
Kojiro Hyuga shot
a powerful kick

198
00:08:13,034 --> 00:08:14,535
towards the other end
of the goal.

199
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,437
Meiwa is up 3-2.

200
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:17,997
Are you okay?

201
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:19,957
Are you okay, Mamoru?
Are you hurt?

202
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,667
I'm okay.

203
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:23,920
Did you see that,
Nankatsu?

204
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:24,837
-Huh?
-Huh?

205
00:08:24,962 --> 00:08:27,298
You just witnessed
my real style of play.

206
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:31,714
Don't mind it.
It's just one goal.

207
00:08:31,739 --> 00:08:32,991
You can tie the match.

208
00:08:33,016 --> 00:08:35,143
Nankatsu goes
on the offense.

209
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:36,476
We won't lose to you.

210
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,560
Teppei!

211
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:41,312
Hajime!

212
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:42,480
I have it!

213
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:44,565
Nankatsu is far
from done.

214
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:46,525
They're looking for
a goal to tie.

215
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:49,415
Listen, everyone, I want you
covering Tsubasa.

216
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:53,016
It's all yours, Taro.

217
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:54,533
The ball is now
in possession of

218
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:55,952
the genius Taro Misaki.

219
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:57,495
But Tsubasa is
totally covered

220
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,622
and that's why he can't
seem to pass the ball.

221
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:00,706
-Huh?
-Huh?

222
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,000
Tsubasa manages
to outdo the defense

223
00:09:03,025 --> 00:09:04,525
with two of
Meiwa's players.

224
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,551
There's no way.

225
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:07,129
Score again!

226
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,945
And he scores with
a beautiful header.

227
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:16,556
Team Nankatsu ties
the score once again.

228
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,640
No...

229
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:19,100
That little twerp!

230
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:23,271
This is a nail-biting match.

231
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,523
Both teams have
their minds set on

232
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:27,024
giving their all
for victory.

233
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:29,402
Everyone is passing
the ball to their captains

234
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,362
to look for
an opportunity to score.

235
00:09:31,754 --> 00:09:33,673
The battle between
Tsubasa Ozora and

236
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,232
-Kojiro Hyuga is intense.
-I won't let you win!

237
00:09:35,257 --> 00:09:36,075
-The scoreboard is
-Me neither!

238
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,535
updating constantly.

239
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:40,371
We don't know what team
will take home the win.

240
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:45,668
And Nankatsu ties
the match once again.

241
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,673
The scoreboard is
a five-all draw.

242
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,550
Neither Tsubasa Ozora
nor Kojiro Hyuga

243
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,468
have given up despite
the terrible heat

244
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:55,469
that surrounds the pitch.

245
00:09:55,469 --> 00:09:56,679
There are five minutes
on the clock

246
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,056
for this fascinating battle
to come to an end.

247
00:09:59,181 --> 00:10:00,516
I'll never let them win.

248
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:03,352
Looks like they're equal
in skill, my lady.

249
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:05,730
Well, actually,
under this boiling heat,

250
00:10:05,955 --> 00:10:07,039
the main factor
for the match

251
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,107
becomes their endurance.

252
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:09,609
I wonder...

253
00:10:10,001 --> 00:10:11,252
which of the two
will overcome

254
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,237
the major setbacks
of this match?

255
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,239
We'll soon find out.

256
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:17,742
I can't lose to him!

257
00:10:18,327 --> 00:10:20,996
Which team will score
with such little time left?

258
00:10:22,638 --> 00:10:24,640
Sawada manages
to outplay Urabe

259
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:26,601
and he moves forward
showing great ball-handling.

260
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:27,960
Over here, Takeshi!

261
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,004
All yours, Kojiro.

262
00:10:30,229 --> 00:10:31,564
Sawada sends
a crossover pass

263
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,548
to Hyuga.

264
00:10:32,573 --> 00:10:33,449
The ball is in the air.

265
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:37,220
I can't afford to
lose this match

266
00:10:37,245 --> 00:10:39,163
under any circumstance!

267
00:10:39,474 --> 00:10:42,268
I won't let
my family down!

268
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,186
It's an airborne battle.

269
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,399
Goal!

270
00:10:50,524 --> 00:10:51,525
Oh!

271
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:53,647
15 minutes into
the second half,

272
00:10:53,672 --> 00:10:56,256
Meiwa scores
a great header.

273
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:58,579
Kojiro's raw strength
won the duel.

274
00:10:58,604 --> 00:10:59,605
Did you see that?

275
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,410
Soccer is a sport
for men only.

276
00:11:01,535 --> 00:11:03,496
It's not a game
for little twerps.

277
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,164
It's not just a game for me.

278
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:06,249
What did you just say?

279
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:07,708
That soccer...

280
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,877
That soccer is my dream!

281
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:12,630
We'll be back
with Captain Tsubasa!

282
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,763
AFFILIATION: MEIWA FC BIRTHDAY: JANUARY 2 HEIGHT: 136 CM WEIGHT: 39 KG BLOOD TYPE: A

283
00:11:22,413 --> 00:11:24,749
There are four minutes
left in the second half,

284
00:11:25,092 --> 00:11:26,635
and everyone is
asking themselves

285
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,178
if Nankatsu
will manage to tie.

286
00:11:28,303 --> 00:11:30,013
Everybody, let's tie
the match first

287
00:11:30,138 --> 00:11:31,056
and then win.

288
00:11:31,081 --> 00:11:33,125
We'll defend our goal,
no matter what happens.

289
00:11:34,101 --> 00:11:37,229
So...soccer is
your dream, Tsubasa?

290
00:11:37,429 --> 00:11:39,264
You're underestimating
the game.

291
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,861
I'll have to teach
you the hard way.

292
00:11:42,716 --> 00:11:44,092
And the match starts again.

293
00:11:44,257 --> 00:11:45,591
Their defense starts
running down the pitch.

294
00:11:45,616 --> 00:11:46,634
All of Nankatsu is
on the offensive.

295
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,575
I know you guys can do it!

296
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,393
Come on! You guys have to
tie the match.

297
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:51,086
You can do it!

298
00:11:51,311 --> 00:11:53,021
You can do it, Tsubasa.
I trust you.

299
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,944
Nankatsu is determined
to score again.

300
00:11:56,147 --> 00:11:57,273
Urabe dribbles the ball

301
00:11:57,298 --> 00:11:59,186
and looks for
an opportunity to pass.

302
00:11:59,211 --> 00:12:00,754
Tsubasa Ozora,
the team's #10,

303
00:12:00,779 --> 00:12:01,738
waits in
the opponent's goal,

304
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:03,073
but Kojiro Hyuga
has him well covered.

305
00:12:03,098 --> 00:12:03,974
Tsubasa...

306
00:12:04,249 --> 00:12:06,084
It doesn't matter how
many passes they make.

307
00:12:06,109 --> 00:12:07,569
I'll stop them all.

308
00:12:09,259 --> 00:12:11,179
Kojiro isn't letting him go.

309
00:12:11,204 --> 00:12:12,163
Be careful, Hanji!

310
00:12:12,188 --> 00:12:13,189
Huh?

311
00:12:13,347 --> 00:12:14,849
And Nankatsu
loses the ball.

312
00:12:14,874 --> 00:12:16,167
Listen up, everyone.

313
00:12:16,192 --> 00:12:18,111
I want all of you
to go on the offense.

314
00:12:18,136 --> 00:12:19,179
-Yeah!
-Yes, Captain!

315
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:21,559
Instead of
playing defense,

316
00:12:21,855 --> 00:12:23,524
Team Meiwa decides to
counterattack

317
00:12:23,549 --> 00:12:25,467
with all they've got
to secure victory.

318
00:12:25,925 --> 00:12:26,926
Yep, that's it.

319
00:12:27,184 --> 00:12:28,624
You have to
keep attacking

320
00:12:28,649 --> 00:12:29,775
and looking to score.

321
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,594
You guys are
the stronger players.

322
00:12:31,871 --> 00:12:32,872
Get back, guys!

323
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:35,422
If they score another goal,
it'll be too hard come back.

324
00:12:38,085 --> 00:12:39,837
Sawada sends
a crossover pass.

325
00:12:40,118 --> 00:12:40,702
I got it!

326
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:42,072
You won't be able
to stop me.

327
00:12:42,097 --> 00:12:43,139
I'm gonna score!

328
00:12:44,593 --> 00:12:46,595
And the ball lands
in the hands of the goalie!

329
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,680
What a great defense!

330
00:12:47,805 --> 00:12:48,639
How did he--?

331
00:12:48,764 --> 00:12:50,182
Great job.
Well done, Yuzo.

332
00:12:50,307 --> 00:12:51,350
That was a great tackle!

333
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:54,857
No way Team Nankatsu
will ever lose to you!

334
00:12:55,038 --> 00:12:56,831
The goalkeeper shoots
the ball and it lands

335
00:12:56,856 --> 00:12:59,069
-at the feet of Misaki.
-I got him.

336
00:12:59,094 --> 00:13:01,735
Misaki passes it
over to Tsubasa,

337
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:04,296
but Hyuga plans
to intercept the ball.

338
00:13:04,321 --> 00:13:05,147
Kojiro!

339
00:13:05,172 --> 00:13:06,924
I'm counting on you,
Tsubasa.

340
00:13:06,949 --> 00:13:07,950
I'm gonna score that goal.

341
00:13:08,033 --> 00:13:08,993
I won't let you, twerp.

342
00:13:09,076 --> 00:13:10,975
This is
the decisive moment.

343
00:13:12,455 --> 00:13:13,831
It's a mid-air duel.

344
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:15,778
It looks like
they're evenly matched.

345
00:13:17,376 --> 00:13:19,530
Both captains go
straight to the floor.

346
00:13:19,712 --> 00:13:21,088
Careful, Tsubasa!

347
00:13:21,959 --> 00:13:24,150
But Tsubasa
quickly recovers!

348
00:13:24,216 --> 00:13:26,260
You can do it, Tsubasa!
Score that goal!

349
00:13:26,385 --> 00:13:27,737
And now,
he has the ball.

350
00:13:27,762 --> 00:13:29,346
He's heading straight
towards Meiwa's goalkeeper

351
00:13:29,371 --> 00:13:30,372
with great speed.

352
00:13:31,056 --> 00:13:32,266
Oh, no, you won't!

353
00:13:32,475 --> 00:13:33,267
Hyuga gets up and

354
00:13:33,292 --> 00:13:34,877
desperately
tries to catch up.

355
00:13:34,902 --> 00:13:36,077
Ladies and gentlemen,

356
00:13:36,102 --> 00:13:39,039
this is
a fast-paced battle.

357
00:13:39,064 --> 00:13:41,233
In order to keep the promise
I made to Genzo,

358
00:13:41,685 --> 00:13:43,062
I have to tie this.

359
00:13:43,277 --> 00:13:45,362
You say that
soccer is your dream?

360
00:13:45,988 --> 00:13:48,032
In soccer,
you can only play to win.

361
00:13:48,324 --> 00:13:49,408
You can't lose.

362
00:13:49,617 --> 00:13:50,618
Not only that...

363
00:13:50,743 --> 00:13:52,369
Tsubasa Ozora...

364
00:13:52,495 --> 00:13:55,289
Prepare yourself because
I'll be the one to win!

365
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,251
Tsubasa
manages to evade

366
00:13:59,276 --> 00:14:00,681
Hyuga's sliding tackle.

367
00:14:00,706 --> 00:14:01,957
This can't be!

368
00:14:02,171 --> 00:14:03,506
The ball is
in the air...

369
00:14:03,531 --> 00:14:04,824
Tsubasa shoots and...

370
00:14:05,508 --> 00:14:07,176
Goal!

371
00:14:08,052 --> 00:14:09,345
And Nankatsu
ties the match

372
00:14:09,370 --> 00:14:11,998
right at the last
second on the clock.

373
00:14:14,266 --> 00:14:15,017
But how?

374
00:14:15,142 --> 00:14:16,977
How did he evade
my sliding tackle?

375
00:14:17,103 --> 00:14:18,312
That's impossible.

376
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,726
I can't...

377
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,775
I can't lose like this.

378
00:14:23,442 --> 00:14:25,277
I can't let
my family down.

379
00:14:29,059 --> 00:14:30,894
That soccer
is my dream.

380
00:14:33,244 --> 00:14:34,537
-Wow, Tsubasa, great job!
-You really did it.

381
00:14:34,562 --> 00:14:37,023
You tied the match, Tsubasa!
Congrats!

382
00:14:37,048 --> 00:14:37,820
Yeah!

383
00:14:37,845 --> 00:14:39,347
After losing to Kojiro,

384
00:14:39,748 --> 00:14:41,333
you learned from
your mistakes.

385
00:14:41,358 --> 00:14:45,148
In the end, you improved
your soccer style.

386
00:14:45,820 --> 00:14:47,376
That's one of
your strengths.

387
00:14:47,733 --> 00:14:49,151
There's still a minute left.

388
00:14:49,176 --> 00:14:50,010
If we attack them,

389
00:14:50,035 --> 00:14:51,745
I'm sure that we can
come out on top.

390
00:14:51,770 --> 00:14:53,342
Let's keep at it.

391
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,660
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

392
00:14:55,162 --> 00:14:56,622
I'm sorry, Captain.

393
00:14:56,725 --> 00:14:57,726
-Takeshi...
-Huh?

394
00:14:58,303 --> 00:14:59,429
When the whistle blows,

395
00:14:59,454 --> 00:15:01,414
I want you to pass me
the ball immediately.

396
00:15:01,439 --> 00:15:02,398
What?

397
00:15:02,398 --> 00:15:03,399
Uh...

398
00:15:05,155 --> 00:15:06,239
Tsubasa...

399
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:09,029
I admit it. I underestimated
you in the beginning.

400
00:15:09,363 --> 00:15:11,115
I got cocky trying
to go head-to-head.

401
00:15:11,632 --> 00:15:13,217
I never imagined that
there'd be someone

402
00:15:13,242 --> 00:15:15,035
in this tournament
who could stop me.

403
00:15:15,965 --> 00:15:17,342
But I'm far from done.

404
00:15:18,164 --> 00:15:19,165
This time around...

405
00:15:19,498 --> 00:15:20,458
you won't get
to stop me.

406
00:15:20,583 --> 00:15:22,168
-Huh?
-He's going to shoot.

407
00:15:23,043 --> 00:15:24,378
I'll show you
the real power

408
00:15:24,378 --> 00:15:26,380
of Kojiro Hyuga!

409
00:15:28,549 --> 00:15:29,341
No!

410
00:15:29,467 --> 00:15:31,302
Hyuga shoots an amazingly
powerful shot

411
00:15:31,427 --> 00:15:32,386
from midfield.

412
00:15:32,386 --> 00:15:34,305
Tsubasa Ozora attempts
to get to the ball.

413
00:15:35,473 --> 00:15:36,891
But he misses!

414
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:41,687
And the ball makes
direct impact

415
00:15:41,712 --> 00:15:42,797
with the goalpost!

416
00:15:44,315 --> 00:15:46,358
Nakayama receives it
and passes the ball,

417
00:15:46,358 --> 00:15:47,835
but just like that,

418
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:50,321
Hyuga intercepts it and
he's determined to score.

419
00:15:50,346 --> 00:15:51,931
The captain from
Meiwa wants the victory.

420
00:15:52,114 --> 00:15:54,283
Kojiro,
you're incredible.

421
00:15:54,325 --> 00:15:56,535
Your determination
and strength are endless.

422
00:15:56,841 --> 00:15:58,259
You're just like Genzo.

423
00:15:58,284 --> 00:15:59,263
Hyuga runs with

424
00:15:59,288 --> 00:16:00,556
determination
towards the goal.

425
00:16:00,581 --> 00:16:02,416
Meanwhile, the ref is
looking at his watch.

426
00:16:05,252 --> 00:16:06,295
Impressive!

427
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:08,397
Tsubasa's in front of
the goal to defend it.

428
00:16:08,422 --> 00:16:11,467
He doesn't plan to
leave it to luck this time.

429
00:16:11,949 --> 00:16:14,487
Hyuga tries to fool him,
but it's futile.

430
00:16:14,512 --> 00:16:17,348
Tsubasa doesn't fall for any
of his opponent's feints.

431
00:16:17,848 --> 00:16:19,350
I won't lose to you.

432
00:16:19,517 --> 00:16:21,227
I won't let you score,
Kojiro.

433
00:16:21,435 --> 00:16:24,238
I will come out on top,
Tsubasa!

434
00:16:24,536 --> 00:16:26,205
Don't give up, Tsubasa!

435
00:16:26,357 --> 00:16:27,566
Do it, Kojiro.

436
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:28,984
Do it, Tsubasa.

437
00:16:29,735 --> 00:16:32,822
The stadium's roars
are literally deafening.

438
00:16:32,988 --> 00:16:34,323
From the start,
it's been a duel

439
00:16:34,323 --> 00:16:36,258
between Tsubasa
and Kojiro.

440
00:16:36,283 --> 00:16:37,535
Both of them
have shown to be

441
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,370
extraordinary players.

442
00:16:39,637 --> 00:16:41,222
But in this last minute,

443
00:16:41,247 --> 00:16:44,250
the winner of this duel
will be decided.

444
00:16:45,035 --> 00:16:46,911
Don't get distracted,
Tsubasa.

445
00:16:46,936 --> 00:16:48,062
Come on, Kojiro.

446
00:16:48,087 --> 00:16:49,380
You have to
take advantage of

447
00:16:49,405 --> 00:16:51,604
any opportunity
to shoot.

448
00:16:53,217 --> 00:16:55,010
No! It looks like
Tsubasa Ozora

449
00:16:55,035 --> 00:16:56,361
took a wrong step.

450
00:16:56,386 --> 00:16:57,721
And now,
he's losing his balance.

451
00:16:58,514 --> 00:16:59,682
This is my opportunity.

452
00:16:59,807 --> 00:17:01,600
Hyuga sees
Tsubasa Ozora's blunder

453
00:17:01,725 --> 00:17:03,853
and winds up for the winning
shot of the match.

454
00:17:04,061 --> 00:17:05,062
Now!

455
00:17:05,396 --> 00:17:06,730
Hyuga can't shoot.

456
00:17:06,856 --> 00:17:08,315
Tsubasa kicks
the ball away with

457
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:09,358
-a miraculous
-No, you won't.

458
00:17:09,483 --> 00:17:10,317
-sliding tackle.
-Damn you, twerp!

459
00:17:10,443 --> 00:17:12,194
You fell down
on purpose.

460
00:17:12,475 --> 00:17:13,518
That's it, Tsubasa!

461
00:17:14,447 --> 00:17:15,990
The ball is now
under the possession

462
00:17:16,015 --> 00:17:17,016
of Shingo Takasugi.

463
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:18,251
The referee is about
to blow the whistle and...!

464
00:17:23,639 --> 00:17:24,640
Huh?

465
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:28,757
-Huh?
-Huh?

466
00:17:31,881 --> 00:17:32,882
Huh?

467
00:17:34,508 --> 00:17:36,343
Goal!

468
00:17:37,636 --> 00:17:38,554
And it's over!

469
00:17:38,679 --> 00:17:41,449
Team Meiwa scored
at the last second.

470
00:17:41,474 --> 00:17:43,225
Team Nankatsu lost!

471
00:17:45,978 --> 00:17:46,979
Oh...

472
00:17:48,189 --> 00:17:48,773
-Oh...
-Oh...

473
00:17:48,898 --> 00:17:51,400
Oh, what a great match,
ladies and gentlemen!

474
00:17:51,425 --> 00:17:53,344
Both teams played
splendidly well.

475
00:17:53,685 --> 00:17:55,896
The captains faced off
in a six-goal duel,

476
00:17:55,921 --> 00:17:57,840
but thanks to
Takeshi Sawada,

477
00:17:57,865 --> 00:18:00,012
Meiwa defeated Nankatsu
by a one goal

478
00:18:00,263 --> 00:18:01,764
making the score 6 to 7.

479
00:18:02,037 --> 00:18:03,205
It's incredible.

480
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:05,149
The first match of
the national tournament

481
00:18:05,174 --> 00:18:07,988
turned out to be
truly spectacular.

482
00:18:09,418 --> 00:18:11,253
Even if Meiwa
won the match,

483
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:13,564
to me, the duel between
Kojiro and Tsubasa

484
00:18:13,589 --> 00:18:14,590
is a draw.

485
00:18:17,676 --> 00:18:18,677
Tsubasa...

486
00:18:19,637 --> 00:18:20,554
Huh?

487
00:18:20,679 --> 00:18:21,388
Oh!

488
00:18:23,432 --> 00:18:24,600
No...

489
00:18:25,935 --> 00:18:26,936
Is he...

490
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,395
crying?

491
00:18:29,230 --> 00:18:30,815
Tsubasa...
Let's get going.

492
00:18:34,893 --> 00:18:38,366
Meiwa, Nankatsu,
you both played well!

493
00:18:38,391 --> 00:18:39,809
What a great match, kids!

494
00:18:41,242 --> 00:18:42,868
The crowd cheers
and applauds

495
00:18:42,993 --> 00:18:44,328
for both teams.

496
00:18:44,328 --> 00:18:46,205
They played like
professionals!

497
00:18:46,247 --> 00:18:49,750
It was a great match,
a real battle of titans.

498
00:18:53,379 --> 00:18:55,673
NANKATSU SC

499
00:18:56,899 --> 00:18:58,442
Why the long face,
everybody?

500
00:18:58,466 --> 00:18:59,376
Don't sweat it.

501
00:18:59,697 --> 00:19:00,907
It doesn't matter
if we lost.

502
00:19:00,932 --> 00:19:02,100
You played your best.

503
00:19:02,674 --> 00:19:04,593
Not everything's lost.
Relax, guys.

504
00:19:04,618 --> 00:19:06,244
This match
doesn't determine

505
00:19:06,269 --> 00:19:08,104
if we're out of
the national tournament.

506
00:19:08,651 --> 00:19:10,486
Oh!
Yeah, that's true.

507
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:13,055
Because in the
elimination phase,

508
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:15,415
two teams from each group
can make it out.

509
00:19:15,626 --> 00:19:17,461
If we win the next
four matches that follow,

510
00:19:17,486 --> 00:19:19,321
we will still be in
the national tournament.

511
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:20,869
Yeah, you're right.

512
00:19:20,894 --> 00:19:22,271
We can still do this.

513
00:19:22,744 --> 00:19:23,745
Tsubasa...

514
00:19:23,770 --> 00:19:24,687
You're the captain.

515
00:19:24,743 --> 00:19:27,065
You can't put all
the blame on yourself.

516
00:19:27,329 --> 00:19:28,873
Leave this defeat
in the past.

517
00:19:28,898 --> 00:19:31,745
What's important now is to
win all the next matches.

518
00:19:32,071 --> 00:19:33,364
If we win our matches,

519
00:19:33,389 --> 00:19:36,511
we can go head-to-head
with Meiwa again later on.

520
00:19:37,506 --> 00:19:38,716
Mhm.

521
00:19:39,483 --> 00:19:41,485
That's it, Captain.
We can still win.

522
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:43,304
Don't get discouraged.
You got that?

523
00:19:46,223 --> 00:19:47,475
Tadashi speaking.

524
00:19:49,660 --> 00:19:51,370
Hey, Yuzo,
this is for you.

525
00:19:51,395 --> 00:19:52,396
Huh?

526
00:19:53,622 --> 00:19:54,707
Yeah, buddy, we lost.

527
00:19:54,732 --> 00:19:56,192
But it was
an incredible match.

528
00:19:56,859 --> 00:19:58,319
You really outdid
yourself, Yuzo.

529
00:19:58,344 --> 00:19:59,577
I'm proud of you.

530
00:19:59,795 --> 00:20:01,297
Thank you so much
for that, Genzo.

531
00:20:01,322 --> 00:20:02,323
-Huh?
-Huh?

532
00:20:02,673 --> 00:20:03,466
I'm asking you...

533
00:20:03,491 --> 00:20:05,286
Take care of our goal
until I can come back.

534
00:20:05,311 --> 00:20:07,063
Yeah!
Don't you worry about it.

535
00:20:07,528 --> 00:20:08,446
It's a deal then.

536
00:20:08,471 --> 00:20:10,014
Can you put
Tsubasa on, please?

537
00:20:10,335 --> 00:20:12,670
Uh... Yeah, I'll put him on.
Just wait.

538
00:20:13,591 --> 00:20:15,134
Hello?
Do you hear me?

539
00:20:15,461 --> 00:20:16,462
Yeah...

540
00:20:17,421 --> 00:20:18,422
Yeah.

541
00:20:18,923 --> 00:20:19,924
Of course.

542
00:20:20,621 --> 00:20:21,622
Leave it all to me.

543
00:20:22,025 --> 00:20:24,361
All we have to do is
win the next four matches,

544
00:20:24,563 --> 00:20:25,982
and we can qualify
for the finals

545
00:20:26,007 --> 00:20:27,008
of the tournament.

546
00:20:27,648 --> 00:20:29,525
Don't you worry.
We'll take care of it, Genzo.

547
00:20:29,550 --> 00:20:30,384
No sweat.

548
00:20:30,588 --> 00:20:32,090
Exactly, we're going to win.

549
00:20:32,328 --> 00:20:33,746
Isn't that right, everyone?

550
00:20:34,239 --> 00:20:35,824
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

551
00:20:36,357 --> 00:20:38,234
I'm counting on
all of you guys.

552
00:20:38,359 --> 00:20:40,402
I'll try to recover
as fast as possible

553
00:20:40,449 --> 00:20:41,491
so I can play
with you all.

554
00:20:42,393 --> 00:20:44,020
We'll win the national
tournament together.

555
00:20:47,451 --> 00:20:49,245
In the first round
of the tournament,

556
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:51,972
Team Furano got
a win over Team Nagano

557
00:20:51,997 --> 00:20:53,958
in their first encounter,
2 to 1.

558
00:20:53,983 --> 00:20:55,276
Nagano couldn't
keep up with

559
00:20:55,301 --> 00:20:56,844
the teamwork of Furano.

560
00:20:57,211 --> 00:20:59,296
And on the other side,
in the fourth group,

561
00:20:59,321 --> 00:21:01,614
Team Musashi goes up
against Team Jonan.

562
00:21:01,841 --> 00:21:03,484
And here is
Prince Jun Misugi

563
00:21:03,509 --> 00:21:05,050
intercepting the ball.

564
00:21:07,346 --> 00:21:08,889
Oh, I'm so jealous!

565
00:21:08,914 --> 00:21:10,511
All the ladies love him.

566
00:21:10,536 --> 00:21:11,537
Huh?

567
00:21:12,643 --> 00:21:14,353
What an elegant feint.

568
00:21:15,187 --> 00:21:16,987
And a beautiful jump.

569
00:21:17,773 --> 00:21:20,317
Jun Misugi plays as if
he were painting a canvas

570
00:21:20,317 --> 00:21:22,319
and all of the crowd
watches the maestro.

571
00:21:22,445 --> 00:21:24,697
Tsubasa, I'm really
looking forward

572
00:21:24,722 --> 00:21:26,265
to get on the pitch
to face you.

573
00:21:27,324 --> 00:21:28,451
Jun Misugi.

574
00:21:31,370 --> 00:21:32,163
Goal!

575
00:21:32,288 --> 00:21:34,373
Team Musashi has
an overwhelming lead

576
00:21:34,398 --> 00:21:35,964
in the beginning
of the match.

577
00:21:36,242 --> 00:21:37,785
That's how
it's done, Captain!

578
00:21:42,298 --> 00:21:45,050
First, it was Kojiro,
and now it's Jun.

579
00:21:45,634 --> 00:21:47,845
I'm sure he'll be
an amazing opponent.

580
00:21:48,596 --> 00:21:49,847
Jun Misugi.

581
00:21:50,549 --> 00:21:52,510
If we want to win
the national tournament,

582
00:21:53,142 --> 00:21:54,852
we'll have to
defeat him first.

583
00:21:59,523 --> 00:22:01,734
I thought I had
everything under control.

584
00:22:02,424 --> 00:22:04,336
My shot was
unstoppable.

585
00:22:07,647 --> 00:22:10,567
Someway, somehow,
he managed to divert it.

586
00:22:11,044 --> 00:22:13,505
He prevented the ball
from going into the goal.

587
00:22:13,788 --> 00:22:15,516
The worst part is that...

588
00:22:17,755 --> 00:22:20,007
I lost the last battle
against him.

589
00:22:21,045 --> 00:22:22,213
Are you Kojiro Hyuga?

590
00:22:22,238 --> 00:22:23,239
Huh?

591
00:22:24,571 --> 00:22:26,573
We've taken an interest
in you, young man.

592
00:22:27,301 --> 00:22:28,677
Are you guys,
player scouts?

593
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:30,221
Yes.

594
00:22:30,971 --> 00:22:33,432
We represent...
the Toho Academy.

595
00:22:35,893 --> 00:22:40,898
[ending theme]
